    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-04-03T09:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-04-03T09:30:00-05:00" n="298"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d298">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.24591/4–346: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-03T18:00:00+03:30"
                            >April 3, 1946—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 31—2:54 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>456. For the Secretary. In press conference today Prince Firuz revealed Ala would
                    inform Security Council that Soviet note of March 24 regarding withdrawal of
                    Soviet troops did not contain any qualifications. This is correct according to
                    information Qavam has recently given me and I do not want you to be misled by
                    statement in first paragraph <gloss target="#t_mytel1">mytel</gloss> 395 March
                    25 to effect that note said Iran would be evacuated “if nothing further
                    happened”. This qualification was not contained in any note and was merely
                    communicated orally to Qavam by Soviet Ambassador when latter called at 10 p.m.
                    March 25, 3 hours after he delivered note.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Murray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
